WEBVTT

00:06.302 --> 00:07.135
You did what?

00:07.137 --> 00:09.171
I married April!

00:09.172 --> 00:11.238
I'm sorry? You carried April?

00:11.240 --> 00:12.506
No. I <i>married</i> her.

00:12.508 --> 00:15.076
My brain cannot even process
the fact that you just said

00:15.078 --> 00:17.945
"married," so I'm assuming
you said "carried,"

00:17.947 --> 00:19.380
like over a big puddle.

00:19.382 --> 00:20.614
Yeah, I did carry her...

00:20.616 --> 00:21.649
Oh.

00:21.651 --> 00:23.417
...into the 'Bago after I married her.

00:23.419 --> 00:25.519
Why?! Why? Why? Why? Why?

00:25.521 --> 00:27.021
Why? Why? Why?!

00:27.023 --> 00:28.389
To piss off Mom!

00:28.391 --> 00:31.525
W-W-Wait! You got married
just to make Mom mad?

00:31.527 --> 00:32.368
Yeah.

00:32.393 --> 00:34.261
Well, what did she
say when you told her?

00:34.263 --> 00:36.364
I didn't tell her yet,
'cause she's gonna be mad.

00:36.366 --> 00:37.431
Yeah.

00:37.433 --> 00:39.400
Getting married to make Mom mad
makes sense.

00:39.402 --> 00:41.102
Look, it just happened, okay?

00:41.104 --> 00:42.670
April and I were in the Winnebago,

00:42.672 --> 00:44.171
talking about how her parents
don't like me

00:44.173 --> 00:45.806
and my parents don't like her,
and I don't know.

00:45.808 --> 00:46.687
We just started feeling like,

00:46.689 --> 00:49.010
"Hey, we don't need anybody.
We got each other."

00:49.012 --> 00:50.878
So, the more we talked about it,
the more upset we got,

00:50.880 --> 00:53.080
and next thing I know,
we're at the courthouse

00:53.082 --> 00:54.849
in this really long line.

00:54.851 --> 00:56.484
And it was around then I started
to have second thoughts,

00:56.486 --> 00:58.452
but if we got out of line,
we'd lose our place,

00:58.454 --> 01:00.755
and everyone else in line
was so happy for us,

01:00.757 --> 01:04.291
'cause we're really young
and hot, and they're all so old.

01:04.293 --> 01:06.660
That's because you're too young
to get married!

01:06.662 --> 01:09.230
You were supposed to date
for 2 1/2 years, graduate,

01:09.232 --> 01:11.665
get a job, and then get married
in a small church,

01:11.667 --> 01:13.934
surrounded by God
and your friends and family

01:13.936 --> 01:15.469
and even the cousins
you don't know very well,

01:15.471 --> 01:17.405
and I am a bridesmaid!

01:17.407 --> 01:19.840
Now, I'll just have to be
a bridesmaid for Cindy

01:19.842 --> 01:22.410
and wear a formal dress
and a safari hat!

01:22.412 --> 01:24.245
It's not about you guys.

01:24.247 --> 01:26.547
It's about me and April, and I love her.

01:26.549 --> 01:28.916
Enough to be married
to her forever, like

01:28.918 --> 01:31.318
"till death do you part" love her?

01:34.489 --> 01:37.391
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

01:37.393 --> 01:38.592
You don't know?!

01:38.594 --> 01:41.629
I don't know, Sue.
Stop nagging me. I got a wife.

01:41.631 --> 01:43.597
Oh, my God! I've got a wife.

01:43.599 --> 01:44.765
Okay. All right.

01:44.767 --> 01:47.268
Let's just take it down for a second.

01:47.270 --> 01:49.670
Okay. Where is April?

01:49.672 --> 01:52.773
Uh, well, after we got married,

01:52.775 --> 01:54.341
we hit a taco truck,

01:54.343 --> 01:56.410
and then I drove her back
to Orson and dropped her off,

01:56.412 --> 01:57.645
'cause she had to work,

01:57.647 --> 01:59.480
but I don't know where she is right now.

02:00.348 --> 02:03.384
Oh, my God. I have a wife
and I have no idea where she is!

02:03.386 --> 02:05.953
Shouldn't I know
where my wife is at all times?

02:05.955 --> 02:08.055
Seriously, Axl, how is this gonna work?

02:08.056 --> 02:09.323
Where are you guys gonna live?

02:09.324 --> 02:10.491
Are you moving in with her?

02:10.493 --> 02:11.759
Is she moving in to the 'Bago?

02:11.761 --> 02:13.060
You guys getting your own place?

02:13.062 --> 02:14.261
Is she gonna take your name?

02:14.263 --> 02:15.996
Are you gonna make her be a Heck?

02:17.199 --> 02:18.666
Oh.

02:20.936 --> 02:23.337
You have to talk to Mom and Dad.

02:23.339 --> 02:25.473
I can't, Sue. I just can't.

02:25.475 --> 02:27.741
Well, you have to. They will understand.

02:27.743 --> 02:29.343
They love you.

02:29.345 --> 02:32.513
A-And, obviously, you're very confused

02:32.515 --> 02:34.448
and conflicted,
because you're hugging me,

02:34.450 --> 02:36.688
and you're not
making any barfing sounds.

02:38.753 --> 02:40.221
Talk to them, Axl.

02:40.223 --> 02:41.989
Ohh.

02:42.958 --> 02:46.127
Oh, hi. Hi. Hi.

02:46.129 --> 02:47.394
Is your mom home?

02:47.396 --> 02:49.797
Um, she didn't say anything
about calling in work

02:49.799 --> 02:51.899
and faking a cold,
so I would go with no.

02:51.901 --> 02:53.200
How about your sister?

02:53.202 --> 02:54.329
- Anyone else home?
- No.

02:54.331 --> 02:55.405
Watch me, Mommy!

02:55.430 --> 02:56.170
- No, watch me!
- Over here, watch me!

02:56.172 --> 02:57.538
No, no. I'm not watching you right now.

02:57.540 --> 02:58.682
I'm talking to this boy.

02:58.684 --> 03:00.975
Hi. How old are you?

03:00.977 --> 03:02.009
15.

03:02.011 --> 03:03.110
You'll do.

03:03.112 --> 03:04.645
I have to take the baby to the doctor.

03:04.647 --> 03:06.614
Would you mind watching the kids
while I'm away?

03:06.616 --> 03:08.182
If I bring them
to the pediatrician's office,

03:08.184 --> 03:09.517
they will tear it to shreds.

03:09.519 --> 03:11.919
I mean, we replaced the fish,
but they're still mad.

03:11.921 --> 03:14.188
But why would they keep cup toys
next to a fish tank?

03:14.190 --> 03:16.357
- Look, Mom, watch me!
- Watch me!

03:16.359 --> 03:18.025
Yeah, I'm watching you!

03:18.027 --> 03:20.094
Uh, I don't think I'm your guy.

03:20.096 --> 03:22.196
- I'm not even allowed to have a hamster.
- Oh, it's fine.

03:22.198 --> 03:24.398
I don't even know where my dog is.

03:24.400 --> 03:27.635
It's fine. It's okay.
It's great. It's fine.

03:27.637 --> 03:29.803
I-I've never babysat before in my life!

03:29.805 --> 03:30.971
It's good. Watch me!

03:30.973 --> 03:33.841
No. The... The boy
is gonna watch you now.

03:33.843 --> 03:35.509
Hey, boy. Hey, boy, look at me!

03:35.511 --> 03:37.077
You might want to watch them.

03:37.079 --> 03:38.612
I'm right here, boy!

03:38.614 --> 03:39.947
Come on!

03:46.621 --> 03:47.688
Hey, buddy, Merry Christmas.

03:47.690 --> 03:48.656
Merry Christmas.

03:48.658 --> 03:50.391
Ah, I got something for you.

03:50.393 --> 03:52.493
Oh. Is this from Paula for Frankie?

03:52.495 --> 03:53.961
No. It's for you.

03:53.963 --> 03:55.396
From who?

03:55.398 --> 03:56.583
Me.

03:57.233 --> 03:58.599
- Why?
- I was at the mall,

03:58.601 --> 04:00.501
and I saw this and thought of you.

04:02.037 --> 04:03.370
Why are you thinking of me?

04:03.372 --> 04:05.472
Come on. Open it.

04:07.842 --> 04:09.674
Sunglasses!

04:10.580 --> 04:11.912
Uh-huh.

04:11.914 --> 04:13.347
You know, I've never seen you
with sunglasses on,

04:13.349 --> 04:15.210
and you're always
kind of squinting, so...

04:15.551 --> 04:17.000
thought you could use them.

04:18.254 --> 04:21.188
Oh. These are nice.

04:21.190 --> 04:22.797
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

04:23.426 --> 04:24.521
Put 'em on.

04:25.027 --> 04:26.460
Nah. It's not that bright out.

04:26.462 --> 04:28.362
You're kind of squinting
a little bit right now.

04:28.364 --> 04:30.130
Come on. Put them on.

04:30.132 --> 04:31.732
I want to see how they look on you.

04:33.101 --> 04:34.435
Nah. I'm fine.

04:34.437 --> 04:35.836
Oh.

04:35.838 --> 04:37.504
All right, then.

04:37.506 --> 04:40.574
Yeah. I'll, uh, I'll see you around.

